ce:section.ce:para:
Venturi tubes made of quartz glass with different geometric parameters (see Scheme 1
                        (a) and Table 1
                        ) are used as HC devices to produce the cavitation effect. The HC reactor using a venturi tube as a cavitation device is shown in Scheme 1(b). The HC reactor is a circulating system consisting of a self-priming pump (1.5 kW, WZB-1500A, Rijin pump Co., Ltd. Japan), a venturi tube, two throttle valves (TV1 and TV2), a flow meter, two pressure gauges (P1 and P2), three thermometers (T1, T2 and T3), a sample catcher, a cooling water circulator and a holding tank. The entire HC reactor is divided into main and bypass lines and each component is connected by PPR pipes with an internal diameter of 19 mm. The function of the self-priming pump is to provide the power for the whole HC system and promote the solution in the holding tank and pipeline to continuously circulate. The throttle valves are used to regulate the flow rate of the liquid flowing through the main and bypass lines. Flowmeter and pressure gauges are used to measure the flow and pressure of the liquid in the main line, respectively. A sample catcher is used to collect the resulting solution. In addition, the HC reactor also includes a cooling water circulator for regulating the solution temperature in the HC system.
